  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Basic introduction to working with maps"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "This tutorial gives a basic introduction to working with gammapy maps, how to fill and visualise data. `gammapy.maps` contains classes to deal with representing pixelized data structures with at least two spatial dimensions representing coordinates on a sphere (e.g. an image in celestial coordinates). This can deal with images (2D), cubes (3D) and hyercubes (3+D).\n",
    "\n",
    "More options to be added as the structure is developed; please see http://docs.gammapy.org/dev/maps/index.html for the latest developments"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "Import the required packages"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from gammapy.data import DataStore\n",
    "from astropy.coordinates import SkyCoord\n",
    "from gammapy.maps import Map, MapAxis, WcsGeom, WcsNDMap, MapCoord\n",
    "import astropy.units as u\n",
    "from gammapy.cube import fill_map_counts, MapMaker"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Data selection\n",
    "\n",
    "We will use one Sgr A* run from the gammapy extra dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#source_pos = SkyCoord.from_name(\"Sgr A*\")\n",
    "source_pos = SkyCoord(266.41681663, -29.00782497, unit=\"deg\")\n",
    "ds=DataStore.from_dir(\"$GAMMAPY_EXTRA/datasets/cta-1dc/index/gps/\")\n",
    "obs=ds.obs(110380)\n",
    "evts=obs.events"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The available columns in the event file can be easily seen. The axes of the maps should be chosen from among these names."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "['EVENT_ID', 'TIME', 'RA', 'DEC', 'ENERGY', 'DETX', 'DETY', 'MC_ID']"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "evts.table.colnames"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Instantiating the Map geometry"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The most common use case is likely to be 3D maps, maps with 2 spatial and one energy dimension. However, there can be many other axes as well, eg: time, phase, telescope type, etc. \n",
    "\n",
    "Here, we will create one 3D map, and, just for example, one 4D map (with energy and MC_ID as the non-spatial dimension)\n",
    "\n",
    "The MapAxis class is used to to create the map axis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "binsz = 0.05 \n",
    "energy_axis = MapAxis.from_bounds(0.5,50.0,10,name='energy',unit='TeV',interp='log')\n",
    "mc_axis=MapAxis.from_edges([0,500,1000,1750], interp=\"lin\", name='MC_ID', unit=None)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A variable bin size can also be put on for different axis, in that case, binsize should be an array of the same dimension, eg:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "binsz_var = np.sqrt((3.0*(energy_axis.center/100.)**-0.8)**2 + 0.1**2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The WcsGeom class will create the required wcs geometry, a geom object"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "geom3d = WcsGeom.create(binsz=binsz, skydir=source_pos, width=15.0,\n",
    "                       axes=[energy_axis])\n",
    "geom4d = WcsGeom.create(binsz=binsz, skydir=source_pos, width=15.0,axes=[energy_axis, mc_axis])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The axes details can be accessed from within the geom object, and the map coordinates for each pixel using the get_coord()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "['energy', 'MC_ID']"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "[_.name for _ in geom4d.axes]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "map4d_coord=geom4d.get_coord()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "lat_cord=map4d_coord.lat"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Filling the Map "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now, we create a map object and fill it the events"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "map3d = WcsNDMap.from_geom(geom=geom3d,unit='')\n",
    "map4d = WcsNDMap.from_geom(geom=geom4d,unit='')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fill_map_counts(map3d,evts)\n",
    "fill_map_counts(map4d,evts)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Exploring maps"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A `repr` of the maps can be easily obtained"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "WcsNDMap\n",
       "\n",
       "\tgeom      : Wcs \n",
       " \tunit      :  \n",
       "\tdata shape: (3, 10, 300, 300)\n",
       "\tdata mean : 3.5e-03 \n",
       "\tdata min  : 0.0e+00 \n",
       "\tdata max  : 6.0e+00 "
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 12,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "map4d"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For a given source pos, the pixel position in the map can be obtained using \n",
    "coord_to_pix(). The geom.to_image() will give create a 2D geometry by dropping all non-spatial dimensions of this\n",
    "geometry."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pix_lon,pix_lat=map4d.geom.to_image().coord_to_pix(source_pos)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The map has (N+2)D dimensions, where the last 2 dimensions are the spatial ones. The shape of the the rest N dimensions in the geom object can be seen using the shape parameter"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(10, 3)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 14,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "geom4d.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In the map object, the non spatial dimensions are transposed"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(3, 10, 300, 300)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 15,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "map4d.data.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Each spatial slice can be extracted in a variety of ways\n",
    "(i) by specifying the slice indices - get_image_by_idx()\n",
    "(ii) by specifying the values at which the slice is required - get_image_by_coord\n",
    "(iii) by specifying the pixels - get_image_by_pix()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "map4d_slice = map4d.get_image_by_idx([0,0])\n",
    "map4d_slice = map4d.get_image_by_coord({'energy': '500 GeV', 'MC_ID': '2'})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The images can then be plotted"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x18195bd0f0>,\n",
       " <matplotlib.axes._subplots.WCSAxesSubplot at 0x18195cff60>,\n",
       " None)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 17,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x18195bd0f0>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "map4d_slice.plot()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This map does not really convey a lot, so we will first make a spatial cutout on our region of interest, and then smooth before plotting for a better visualisation "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "map4d_cutout=map4d.make_cutout(position=source_pos,width=7.0*u.deg)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "WcsNDMap\n",
       "\n",
       "\tgeom      : Wcs \n",
       " \tunit      :  \n",
       "\tdata shape: (3, 10, 140, 140)\n",
       "\tdata mean : 1.2e-02 \n",
       "\tdata min  : 0.0e+00 \n",
       "\tdata max  : 6.0e+00 "
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 19,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "map4d_cutout"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x1819d3c358>,\n",
       " <matplotlib.axes._subplots.WCSAxesSubplot at 0x1819d40f28>,\n",
       " <matplotlib.colorbar.Colorbar at 0x1819e5f7b8>)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 20,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x1819d3c358>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "map4d_slice=map4d_cutout.get_image_by_coord({'energy': '500 GeV', 'MC_ID': '2'})\n",
    "map4d_slice.smooth(radius=0.2*u.deg,kernel=\"gauss\").plot(add_cbar=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Reprojecting maps onto a different geometry"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "It is often useful to reproject the maps onto different geometries. Here, we will reproject our map onto a Galactic Coordinate system"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "geom_rep = WcsGeom.create(binsz=binsz, skydir=source_pos,coordsys=\"GAL\", width=15.0,axes=[energy_axis, mc_axis])\n",
    "map_rep = map4d.reproject(geom_rep)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x11065f4a8>,\n",
       " <matplotlib.axes._subplots.WCSAxesSubplot at 0x181998fef0>,\n",
       " None)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 22,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x11065f4a8>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(30,20))\n",
    "ax1=fig.add_subplot(121,projection=geom4d.wcs)\n",
    "map4d.get_image_by_coord({'energy': '500 GeV', 'MC_ID': '2'}).smooth(radius=0.2*u.deg,kernel=\"gauss\").plot(ax=ax1)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax2=fig.add_subplot(122,projection=geom_rep.wcs)\n",
    "map_rep.get_image_by_coord({'energy': '500 GeV', 'MC_ID': '2'}).smooth(radius=0.2*u.deg,kernel=\"gauss\").plot(ax=ax2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Reading images from fits files"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "It is very simple to read fits files from already prepared data sets as well.\n",
    "As an example, we will read a FITS file from a prepared Fermi-LAT 2FHL dataset:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "vela_2fhl = WcsNDMap.read(\"$GAMMAPY_EXTRA/datasets/fermi_2fhl/fermi_2fhl_vela.fits.gz\", hdu='COUNTS')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can see the geometry and the shape of the map"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "WcsNDMap\n",
       "\n",
       "\tgeom      : Wcs \n",
       " \tunit      :  \n",
       "\tdata shape: (180, 320)\n",
       "\tdata mean : 2.7e-02 \n",
       "\tdata min  : 0.0e+00 \n",
       "\tdata max  : 4.0e+00 "
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 24,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "vela_2fhl"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "WcsGeom\n",
       "\n",
       "\tnpix      : 320 x 180 pix\n",
       "\tcoordsys  : GAL\n",
       "\tprojection: CAR\n",
       "\tcenter    : 266.0 deg, -1.2 deg\n",
       "\twidth     : 32.0 x 18.0 deg\n",
       "\tndim      : 2\n",
       "\taxes      : "
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 25,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "vela_2fhl.geom"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since this is a 2D map in the first place, we can make some nice plots (no slicing required)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x11065f240>,\n",
       " <matplotlib.axes._subplots.WCSAxesSubplot at 0x18199a6198>,\n",
       " None)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 26,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x11065f240>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "vela_2fhl.smooth(kernel='gauss', radius=0.5 * u.deg).plot()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Plotting contours"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Lets try to plot some contours now! We will read a second image containing WMAP data from the same region, and overlay WMAP contours on top of the Fermi image. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "WcsGeom\n",
       "\n",
       "\tnpix      : 300 x 300 pix\n",
       "\tcoordsys  : CEL\n",
       "\tprojection: TAN\n",
       "\tcenter    : 128.5 deg, -45.8 deg\n",
       "\twidth     : 30.0 x 30.0 deg\n",
       "\tndim      : 2\n",
       "\taxes      : "
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 27,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "vela_wmap = WcsNDMap.read(\"$GAMMAPY_EXTRA/datasets/images/Vela_region_WMAP_K.fits\")\n",
    "vela_wmap.geom"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As you can see, these two images have a different geometry. This is where reprojection comes in handy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "vela_wmap_rep = vela_wmap.reproject(vela_2fhl.geom)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "vela_pos = vela_2fhl.geom.center_skydir"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.contour.QuadContourSet at 0x181a0d62e8>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 30,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x181a0d5c88>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax, _ = vela_2fhl.make_cutout(vela_pos, width=9.0 * u.deg).smooth(kernel='gauss', radius=0.5 * u.deg).plot()\n",
    "ax.contour(vela_wmap_rep.make_cutout(vela_pos, width=9.0 * u.deg).data, cmap='Blues')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Combining multiple observations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Multiple observations can be combined, and, counts, background and exposure maps created using the MapMaker class"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "/Users/asinha/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/h5py/__init__.py:36: FutureWarning: Conversion of the second argument of issubdtype from `float` to `np.floating` is deprecated. In future, it will be treated as `np.float64 == np.dtype(float).type`.\n",
      "  from ._conv import register_converters as _register_converters\n"
     ]
